inn1.comm: swing and seam! Back of a length outside off, nibbles away and heats the outside edge
and now some extra bounce from short of a length, Roy keen to come forward and has to take his bottom hand off the bat as he defends
some width offered this time, cut through backward point to get England up and running
a lovely piece of timing as he gets a touch too straight and is tucked through square leg
back outside off, left alone
full outside off, 80mph, he defends on the walk into the covers
over the wicket, there's some swing, but it started down the leg side
adjust his line nicely, outside off, left alone by Hales
full at the stumps, 84mph, clipped to midwicket
pushed across outside off, a touch shorter, Hales went to cut it through the off side but plays underneath the ball
full at middle and off, 86mph, defended with an open face towards backward point
sends down his first bouncer, good pace at 86mph and well directed over off stump, Hales drops his hands and sways out of the line
very full outside off, Hales jabs over the top of it without making contact...a decent start from Wheeler
short of a length at the body, Roy gets inside the line and tucks down to long leg
nearly pops a return catch, pushes a fraction early at a fuller delivery and it travels just to the left of Southee
lovely punchy drive, it wasn't a half volley, he came forward and played it on the up straight of mid-off
short of a length at off stump, defended into the covers...the sun peeps through for the first time today
a bouncer over off stump, Hales considers a pull but lets it go through to the keeper
angled into the pads, flicked wide of square
close! Almost gets through with a low full toss, hint of late swing as Roy drives around the delivery which dipped on him that's millimetres from off stump
uses his feet and comes down on a line outside leg stump then steers a length delivery to third man
gets too straight onto the pads and that's neatly flicked away fine of long leg who is quite square
full outside off, driven in the air over backward point down to third man
full outside off, 83mph, onto the front foot and defends to mid-off
on middle and off, defended into the leg side
too short, sits up nicely outside off stump and Hales cuts firmly in front of point...another quick outfield
over compensates and gets onto the pads, tucked in front of square
full outside off, driven sweetly from the front foot straight to mid-off but they are able to steal a single
wide outside off, swings further, Roy chases it and doesn't get particularly clse
tighter to off stump, driven to mid-off
full and speared down the leg side, big wide, Southee hasn't found his consistency yet
a rather headless charge to a length delivery, not sure he was watching the ball as he tried to heave to the leg side
a good bouncer, over middle and off, Hales jerks his head out of the line
fuller outside off, cut to backward point
he's connected with this one, another short ball but not a full-on bouncer, it's angled across Hales but he fetches it from outside off high over square leg
another strong pull, this time it's a skimmer along the ground, rolls his wrists well, and finds deep square who had just been sent out
full outside off, punched between cover and mid-off...McCullum keeps them to a single
a maiden international wicket! Nicely done from Wheeler. A length delivery angled across Hales who pushes a little meekly outside off and it travels at a good height to second slip. Scrambled seam.
on a length at off stump, defended back to the bowler
and another! Two quick wickets...a full delivery which nips back into Roy and scoots past the inside edge of an expansive drive to disturb the woodwork
gets a bouncer first up, over leg stump, he ducks
full outside off, left alone
a touch wider outside off, through to the keeper
back of a length at off stump, defended to the covers...excellent over from Southee
back of a length, gets an inside edge into his pads
stays on the back foot and cuts towards point where Guptill's dive can't stop it cleanly
back of a length outside off, opens the face and gets it wide of backward point
full on the stumps, defended into midwicket
hint of width outside off, finds backward point
more seam movement, nips back into Root and takes a thick inside edge to the leg side
quite full outside off but Morgan stays deep and cuts to backward point

fantastic delivery! A late swinging yorker which jams into Morgan's boot, but was it bat first? New Zealand call for a review. It's pad first on first glance. This could be trouble for Morgan. Has it hit in line. No, it's umpire's call on impact and is actually missing off stump
drops it in short, Morgan rolls his wrists and finds deep square
full at the stump, straightens on Root but it's sweetly turned away wide of square leg
full outside off, shaping away, left alone
opens the face off the back foot and finds third man
full on the stumps, defended into midwicket
flicked off the pads to long leg
full outside off, onto the front foot and drives but gets a thick inside edge into his boot
uses his feet and then defends a back of a length delivery
full outside off, 83mph, left alone
another one through to the keeper outside off, a very solid spell from Wheeler
full on middle, defended back to the bowler
touch shorter outside off, punched into the covers
there's some power, throws his hands through a full, wide delivery and dispatches it through the covers
gets too straight this time and Root tickles it down the leg side, out of a reach of a diving Ronchi
better line and length, full outside off, left alone
full outside off, jabbed towards mid-off
comes down the pitch and lofts a length delivery over the off stump, doesn't come out of the screws and is hauled in close to the rope
short of a length outside off, defended towards backward point
onto the back foot and punched to the covers
goes fuller this time, Root is forward and drives to mid-off
short delivery on an off-stump line, pulled well in front of square through midwicket
gets lucky with this one as he uses his feet and then gets an inside edge just wide of the stumps which trickles to fine leg
starts short of a length on leg stump, clipped off his hip by Morgan - in fact he doesn't make contact - and it beats a diving McClenaghan at fine leg. Made a bit of a mess of it.
that's better, short of a length outside off, nips back and cramps Morgan little who deflects it towards slip
uses his feet and slices a length delivery square through the off side, third man comes around
full on middle and off, 85mph, defended into midwicket
lovely stroke, punches a full delivery through the covers with technically very correct cover drive...waited for the ball and played it under his eyes
full and slips it down the leg side
and he'll have to bowler another one, a bouncer is called wide
another bouncer, and another wide...it's becoming a long over. Morgan considered a pull but bailed out and dropped his hands
pitches full, Morgan starts coming down the pitch very early and then shovels it straight of mid-off
driven in the air! But wide of point, was played on the up by Root and he managed to find the gap
shorter this time, much more control in this short as he square drives off the back foot and places it wide of point
fuller outside off, that's a better length, defended with an open face
back of a length on off stump, punched into the covers
dragged down short, Root rolls his wrists and pulls backward of square
full at off stump, defended to the covers
full and angled into the pads, flicked to deep square leg...brings up the fifty stand at a run a ball
full outside off, 87mph, defended to the off side
beats him outside off as Root misses his good at a shorter, wider delivery...didn't get bounce as Root expected
tighter line, neatly punched off the back foot to the cover sweeper
full outside off, drives off a thick outside edge down to third man
straighter delivery which is defended back down the pitch
down the track to lift this from outside off wide of deep cover for a couple
tighter line just defended here
slightly straighter, this is tapped into midwicket for a sharp single, too sharp and Morgan was gone with a direct hit at the non-striker's end
nicely bowled, full length slips past the outside edge
fuller and straighter, this is clipped out wide of deep square and they can come back for two here
off stump line, this is blocked out to backward point
full length just outside off, this is dug out into the covers
straighter line and this is worked out through midwicket, they can get back for three here
middle and off line, this is tucked out through midwicket for two more
pushes hard at one that might have bounced a touch, takes a thick outside edge and runs through cover
tries to come down the pitch, bowler cramps him up and Morgan just taps this out into the covers
back of a length, turned down to long leg on the bounce
handsome drive and well saved by mid-off diving to his left
touch wide and Root lays into a cover drive wide of the sweeper for a couple to bring the hundred up, decent comeback from this pair so far, 37 balls for the second fifty
Root gets across the off stump to flick another full ball past mid-on, timed so well and it races away from two fielders chasing back, fine stroke
around the wicket, wide line, Root misses trying to cut
similar line, much fuller, this is angled out down to third man
short ball around off stump, Root pulls out of a hook
full length on the stumps, this is flicked out to deep square
full length a foot outside off, very smartly driven to short extra-cover and Kane Willamson makes a fine save down low to his left
slides this further across the leftie who leaves alone
down the wicket, slightly cramped for room so Morgan waits and angles this down to third man
foot outside off, this is flicked off the back foot to backward point
bounces a touch off a straight line, Root gets it down through midwicket and they take an easy single
around the wicket, low full toss clipped down to long-on
step outside leg, this is fired in full and Morgan digs it out back to the bowler
down the track and lifts this handsomely over wide long-on, lovely strike, first six of the innings
frees up the off side and just drives to mid-off this time
step outside leg yet again, this cramps Morgan up a little but he adjusts to touch through midwicket
full just outside off, this is pressed to short extra-cover
waits in the crease for this and carves only to backward point
wider line, Morgan leans out to drive this to deep cover
just a touch short and Root able to rock back and steer this to deep cover
bumper down the leg side, wide on two counts probably
back of a length around off stump, Morgan taps this too close to midwicket to consider a single
wider line outside off, Morgan reaches for it and slaps out on the bounce to the off side sweeper
off stump line, Root pushes up to mid-on
foot down leg
not too different a ball but Morgan stepped outside leg here and tapped it back to the bowler
down the track, this is fired down the leg side and a missed stumping. Morgan well out of his ground and Ronchi couldn't gather going to his right
down leg to the right-hander, another wide
back foot punch, in the air for a time but short of the bowler
down the track and punches this to extra-cover
length ball punched out too close to deep cover for a second here
leg stump line, flicked out to long-on
floated onto leg stump, this is eased down to Root's long-on
full length on the stumps, driven up past mid-on for a single
full, swinging into the front pad, huge cry for lbw, not out given, I was giving it out but maybe it pitched outside leg, New Zealand have no reviews left
similar ball, this time dug out through square leg
up on his toes to cut out to deep cover, fifty for Root in 52 balls, nice innings yet again
full again to Morgan, this is touched up to mid-on's left for a quick single
middle and leg line, this is clipped out to deep square and they can't get back for the second
forward pressing up to short midwicket
tries to create space outside off now but only finds short extra-cover
fuller ball driven down to log-on
full length just wide of off stump, this is driven to backward point

steps outside leg again, Santner follows him, this is driven back to the bowler's left hand and it carried to the bowler so a drop although very tough with one hand and he did get there but it didn't stick
ever-so-slightly short, this is pulled out to deep square
full length just outside off, this is driven to short extra-cover
goes to drive from just outside off, this takes a thick inside edge to midwicket
down the track and hammers a full ball straight to mid-off
back of a length, this is pulled and misses
similar length but wide enough to cut this, finds third man
full length just outside off, played forward out through the covers for a single
full length on leg stump, this is clipped down to long-on

down the pitch looking to clip this leg side, it holds up slightly and takes the pad into leg stump! The breakthrough from Santner and he's bowled well to tie down the batsmen, pressure coming at both ends and Root has fallen trying to create something here. Looking to turn this out down towards long-on, he's been beaten on the inside edge and this takes a clip of the back pad into the top of leg stump
full length a foot outside off, Stokes blocks it firmly back to the bowler
straighter line, this is worked out to deep midwicket
strikes the pad looking to whip this away to leg
goes to sweep and misses, strikes the top of the front pad and almost runs back onto the stumps, Morgan has to be alert to clip this away from the off stump
length ball sliding across the right-hander who drives out to deep cover
down the pitch looking to slap this straight back over the bowlers head, misses
bumper around off stump, Morgan sways inside the line
this is worked with the angle from around middle out wide of mid-on
length ball a foot wide of off stump, this is a mistimed cut to cover-point who is in quite short
shorter length and Morgan delicately lifts it over slip, nicely played, using the pace, a little uppercut sails away for four
slips down the leg side
off stump now, this is driven firmly back to the bowler
similar line, this is a big slog sweep and Stokes gets all of it over midwicket, sails back, first real go at Santner for a while
leg stump line, this is flicked towards square leg who gets down low to his left to make a fine save
hangs back and touches this in front of square leg this time
back in the crease working this back to the bowler
down the track, flicks this off his pads wide of square leg and they can get back for a second here
short ball wide of off stump, Stokes pulls out of a hook and wants a wide but isn't going to get one
has a go at this but only gets it off the toe of the bat through cover
full length a foot outside off, this is driven back to the bowler who saves with a left hand
wide line, cut only down to third man for a single
straight drive back past the bowler, mid-on's dive to his left can only parry this so they get back for a second
width to work with now and unlike Morgan, Stokes finds the gap between third man and deep cover-point, well-timed
full length a foot outside off, this is eased to short extra-cover
back of a length, Morgan stays leg side of this and angles it down to backward point
wider line and this is slashed to backward point again where Guptill gets down low to his right to save well
steps outside leg and drives this down to long-on
goes to reverse sweep and gets it from off stump past short third man and backward point, slapped away off a length, incredible shot really
around the wicket, slow delivery just outside off, this is dabbed into the covers
round the wicket, pushed down to long-off to take him to another fifty...this one from a relatively sedate 67 balls
width outside off, slapped hard towards cover where McCullum parries it behind him
slides on with the air, Morgan gives himself a touch of room and places it through the covers, wide of the sweeper
dragged down very short, cut off the front foot fairly straight through the off side and wide enough of long-off for a brace
again, too short, and this time cut behind point
manages to get this one fuller, pushed to the covers
full at the stumps, driven down to long-off
strong shot, picks up a full delivery and lofts it straight down the ground to bisect long-on and long-off
that was sweetly struck, too, as he gave himself room to the leg side and drilled a full delivery but straight to civer
another one straight down the ground and strikes the boundary marker on the full, gentle medium-pace pitched up to Morgan is much to his liking
drags the length back a fraction, driven into the off side
yorker outside off, dug out down the ground so he keeps the strike...productive over for England
dragged down short again, Morgan pulls in the air over midwicket and just manages to split long-on and deep midwicket as they ran around the rope
cut to backward point
tighter to the batsman, Williamson dives across in his follow through
uses his feet, it's a little shorter than he expected and gets an inside edge to the leg side
again the bowler does the field as this is pushed just to the off side

huge wicket! Morgan going so nicely but has played a slog sweep and missed. It was in his arc, he just appeared to swing over the top of the ball. He is furious with himself. Perhaps got a little frustrated after four dot balls.
back of a length, worked into midwicket
full, angled into the pads, very sweetly flicked away through midwicket and the sweeper only just manages to haul it in
slides this one down the leg side
full outside off, 84mph, driven firmly to mid-off
short outside off, Stokes upper-cuts over backward point, placing it between third man and deep cover
power straight down the ground, a simple thump straight of mid-on as Wheeler goes full outside off, Stokes dragged it a little to the on side...solid connection
and now he cuts a shorter delivery square through off side, good placement again and the wicket is followed by an expensive over
uses his feet straight, then tickles a short-of-a-length delivery to fine leg
bouncer over off stump, 81mph, Buttler sways out of the line
a fuller delivery and it's nicely timed wide of mid-on with a bottom-handed flick
full outside off, pushed to short cover
full, just sliding down the leg side as it takes Buttler on the pads as he tries to work to leg
comes forward and pushes back to the bowler
short of a length outside off, cut very strong but straight to backward point
shuffles to the leg side then opens his face to a short-of-a-length delivery and finds third man
goodness me! Although he shouldn't really be surprised. Buttler moves to the off side then scoops a reasonably short delivery over the wicketkeeper's head
mistimes a pull towards mid-on, Buttler gets the dive out but Southee didn't pick it up cleanly
finds the gap, another delivery back-of-a-length and Stokes pulls just straight of mid-on, was in the air and not sure he meant it exactly
that's even better! Scythes a full delivery through the off side with a skimming extra-cover drive...that's a statement at the start of the Powerplay
boundaries are flowing as Buttler crunches a short delivery through the covers with a flat-batted drive
edged! Southee gets one with a short, wide delivery which Buttler chases and gets a thin edge to the keeper...bowler can't say he planned for that, but New Zealand won't care
appeal for lbw first ball, went for the yorker and took the pad on the full but was heading comfortably down the leg side
good delivery, aiming for another yorker, it's on target and Billings digs it out to mid-on
he's off the mark with a clip off his toes to deep square
aiming full again, Stokes flicks a low full toss out to deep midwicket
full at the stumps and Stokes heaves another boundary straight down the ground...wasn't far off target from McClenaghan but Stokes got fantastic power in the shot
ouch! This is a big full toss which Stokes misses and the ball slams into his leg, leaving him in a heap but he's up pretty quickly
well bowled, giving himself some room to the leg side and McClenaghan follows him with a yorker outside leg stump
short of a length outside off, hammered but straight to cover
that's huge! Almost into the takeaway good stalls over deep midwicket. Back-of-a-length delivery picked up over the leg side with a might swing and what a way to move to fifty
aims for a yorker, comes out as another full toss which is clubbed to deep midwicket
starts with a very short bouncer over leg stump which is too short
a rather ungainly heave into the leg side, loses control as his bottom hand comes off the bat
tight run, which started with Billings trying to sweep a length ball and Stokes calls him through...might have been close if Henry had managed to flick the ball into the stumps
he's off the ground as he pulls down to long-on
full outside off and driven through the covers
he tried the slog sweep earlier, this time he connects, down on one knee and lofts it high over midwicket
well bowled, full outside leg stump, drilled down to long-on
comes round the wicket, sends down another big full toss which Stokes can only swing deep into the leg side off the toe of the bat
uses his feet then drives this in the air wide of mid-off, not quite the timing to reach the boundary as McCullum produces another fully-committed chase
full outside off, clubbed through the leg side
fantastic from Billing as he moves across to the off side and then scoops over short fine-leg...anything Buttler can do
stays in a more conventional position this time but the result is the same as he pulls a short-of-a-length delivery wide of mid-on
another one over fine leg! What confidence from Billings, taking advantage of the short length which another scoop behind square on the leg side
bumper that Stokes gets underneath, Bruce Oxenford consults with his parter and then calls a wide
full delivery, big swing down the ground, hasn't got all of this Stokes but it lands safe out of the reach of long-on
runs this straight to long-on now from a very full delivery around off stump
not too inventive this but it's four, coming down the track and whacking a length ball well over mid-on
goes down on one knee looking to sort of paddle sweep, gets a thick top edge from a length ball over the keeper, fifty stand in just 28 balls
very full and wide of off stump, Billings leaning across to this plays and misses
not as full, this is clean strike down the ground, hasn't got all of it but still enough bat to clear mid-off for a one-bounce four
full length on the stumps, Stokes steps away to leg and creams this over extra-cover, right off the meat of the bat
down to long-off this time, one bounce to the fielder
goes to reverse sweep, extraordinary from Billings, misses though and it takes the bicep to the keeper

length ball outside off, Billings swings hard at it and gets a thick outside edge that loops to short third man. Jaunty little knock from Billings, best we've seen from him so far this series but miscues this, swinging at a ball wide of the stumps, a whirl of a top edge presented a straightforward chance for the fielder
steps across the stumps looking to flick to the leg side, thick inside edge to short long leg, Stokes sent back wanting a single that was never there, a direct hit would have had him
low full toss just outside off, this is clipped out once bounce before deep midwicket
very full at the pads, takes a deflection wide of the keeper for a leg bye

short ball angled in at the body, this is angled straight to backward point! And Rashid fails here, going first ball, couldn't keep this down and steered this straight to the fielder, big wicket for New Zealand. Rashid was cramped up, tried to angle this down to third man but found the fielder
bumper over leg stump, Willey ducks
fuller length chipped leg side and almost carries this to midwicket, just short
wider line and this is forced out past cover
full and wide, leaned out for and dug out to cover
length ball slapped inside mid-off and they take a sharp single, just what Willey needs to do
clears the front leg and swings hard to leg, mistimes this down to long-on
short ball drifts down the leg side but the bowler gets away with it, Willey missed with a hook too
short again, pulled hard, deep square is Elliott going to his right and lets it slip under his hands, not the best work
another pull, not a firm this time and easy for Elliott to field this at deep square

full on leg stump, Stokes goes to smash it down the ground, misses and loses his leg stump! Another wicket down and England ambitions of 350 are surely now scuppered. Stokes continuing to go for his shots and has simply missed a quick straight delivery here, stepping to leg and aiming straight again, Wheeler on the mark and takes out leg stump, another big wicket
full just outside off, this is slapped down to long-on
low full toss, flicked wide of short long leg for a quick single

back of a length, a big swing, gets it high in the air and mid-on takes the catch. Another wicket and England are being whittled away here, easy catch for McCullum. Very poor connection from Willey, the delivery got up too high to control it and this came off high on the bat and looped up to the fielder
length at the pads, this is tickled leg side and well saved from short long leg
very full at the off stump, this is dug out down the ground to long-on
foot outside off on a length and Finn with a flourish shoulders arms
low full toss on the stumps, this is clipped out to deep midwicket

full at the off stump, Finn misses and loses his off stump! Well what a collapse this has been. Finn playing all around a straight ball really, out goes the off stump and New Zealand have polished this off very nice indeed. Southee full and straight, hits the top of off stump, nicely bowled and too good for Steven Finn

inn2.comm: short of a length outside off and crunched to cover from the back foot
angled down the leg side and New Zealand up and running
short of a length, nips into Guptill and takes him on the body
fuller at off stump, onto the front foot and pushes firmly into the covers
back of a length, defended
touch shorter, angled into leg stump, he goes for a whip-pull but it just takes thigh guard into the leg side
just out of reach! He goes for a pull against a short-of-a-length delivery, it takes a top edge but loops over the in-field and Hales can't get back in time
good start on off stump, defended to covers
he strikes! Key early wicket, well bowled. A full length, straightened nicely into Guptill off the seam and that's heading for middle stump. Guptill didn't even contemplate the review
nicely bowled again, full at off stump with just a hint of movement, defended to mid-on
tight to off stump, 82mph, defended to the covers
too straight this time, flicked off the pads to long leg
turned around the corner behind square on the leg side
full outside off, 88mph, onto the front foot and defends
touch of extra bounce from a good length but Williamson adjusts well and tucks it fine on the leg side
very full outside off, driven to mid-off
short in length outside off, defended with soft hands into the point area
a full delivery, plays this a fraction early and nearly bunts a catch back to Finn but just holds back on the shot long enough
outside off, left alone
beaten! Another lovely delivery from Willey who is getting it to move. Nips back from a good length and nearly grazes the inside edge
full outside leg, glances off the pad (or boot) very fine but Finn manages to chase it down
just short! Pushed across full outside off, Williamson drives but it lands just in front of Roy at backward point
short of a length outside off, punched sweetly off the back foot towards cover when Billings pulls off an excellent diving save...a few smiles around as the throw goes a little wrong
left alone outside off
terrific bowling, this delivery climbs from back of a length and flies over Williamson's outside edge as he's drawn into playing away from his body
back of a length, nudged square into the leg side
full and straight, worked towards mid-on
short of a length outside off, Williamson onto his toes and defends towards point
nice piece of timing and placement, full and a touch too straight from Finn which allows Williamson to clip it wide of mid-on
back outside off, short of a length, pushed square into the off side
dropped in short and McCullum doesn't miss out as he dispatches a pull to deep square
shovelled into the leg side
pushed across full outside off, left alone
sweet, sweet timing as he punches a short-of-a-length delivery square through the off side
fuller and tighter to off stump, met with a straight-bat push towards mid-off
full, straight and crunched down the ground by McCullum although he didn't quite time it cleanly
now he's on the charge, down the pitch outside leg stump, the ball was quite wide and he ends up reaching for it and the shot comes off the toe end over cover
excellent start, in the channel outside off, 89mph, and skims past the outside edge
angled into the pads, deflects behind square on the leg side

given lbw! Nips back off a length and hits him on the knee roll. McCullum trapped on the crease. Wood takes out a big fish. McCullum chatted with Williamson about the review but then walked off. The replay confirms it was clipping leg stump
full at off stump, 92.5mph, defended on the front foot...very impressive pace, and right on target straight away
well bowled, a short delivery, takes the top of the bat as Taylor defends down in front of him
angled into the pads, runs into the leg side
full and driven back to the bowler
on a length outside off, 83mph, defended with an open face to backward point
short of a length, pushed to the off side
chopped down to third man
full outside off, he comes forward and the ball slides off the face down to third man
push-and-run into the off side
short ball, 88mph, swatted through square leg with a pull
pulls through midwicket this time, was rushed into the shot a little but managed to keep it under control
and now he drives a slightly fuller delivery through a large gap at cover, certainly not a bad ball
now he pulls again through square leg, looks keen to put bat to ball
full outside off, Taylor walks into a defensive push which finds mid-on
another one clocks at 91mph, defended easily enough into the off side
back of a length, whipped through midwicket
superb shot as he effortlessly punches an over-pitched delivery straight down the ground
a short ball is costly again, pulled in the air through square leg and Finn almost makes a terrific save but his second flick at the ball is when he's on contact with the rope
slower ball, full outside off, worked into the leg side
tucks a back-of-a-length delivery to short midwicket
full on leg stump, flicked away fine of deep square so he can come back for a second
a good, fullish, testing length around off stump, Taylor defends to the off side
full outside off, 90mph, defended back from where it came
closes the face on this one and tucks it away from off stump through midwicket
gets squared up a touch this time by a length delivery and it takes a leading edge towards the off side
back of a length outside off, 88mph, defended to the covers
goes fuller at off stump, 91mph, driven to the covers
starts with a dragged down offspinner-type delivery, he often starts with one of those, which is worked through midwicket
beats Taylor's cut, perhaps not quite as short as he thought...skids through nicely
hint of turn from this legspinner, cut to point
well, well! Buttler almost pulls off a blinder. He saw that Taylor was going down very early for a paddle sweep, Buttler was quickly out from his position and managed to get a glove on it
short and cut to deep cover
pushed down the leg side, nudged backward of square
full and straight, tucked wide of mid-on
nearly drags this one, not for the first time, as he's forcing into the off side from the back foot
dragged short and wide outside off, Taylor plays over the top of the ball
back of a length on off stump, takes a thick outside edge along the ground to point
full outside off, driven into the covers where Billings makes a good save
works a straight delivery to midwicket
edged! But wide of the lone slip, full outside off and Taylor driving forcefully...would probably have been wide of a second, too
short outside off, cut to deep cover
full on off stump, he leans well forward to defend
good cricket, Taylor uses his feet but it's a slightly shorter delivery so he adjusts and defends
full and eased down to long-off
that was nicely bowled, hint of loop, but brilliantly played by Williamson as he came down the pitch, kept his shape, then lofted the ball inside-out over cover
worked to the leg side
short and wide, poor delivery, cut through point with minimal fuss
short again, touch closer to Taylor but he is still able to crunch it square of the wicket...poor start by Finn
better length, fuller at off stump, defended
on off stump, 83mph, defended
full outside off, worked into the leg side
a better finish to the over than the start, defends a delivery on off stump to the covers
length ball just outside off, delicately back-cut and it runs away down towards third man
paddle swept off the stumps, just a single this time to deep square
straight line pushed out down to long-off
back on the stumps turning this out wide of midwicket
pitched up outside off and smartly driven wide of deep cover, great timing, beats the sweeper's slide
bit more air, Taylor forward gets a thick outside edge to backward point
back of a length, pulled out straight to deep square
fuller length just outside off, thick outside edge down to third man
tight off stump line, this is just blocked out into the covers
too straight, this is clipped backward of deep square for an easy couple
foot outside off, this is played late and dropped down towards third man before backward point comes across to field
back foot press into the covers, finds the gap for a quick single
floated up outside off, this is driven against the turn past mid-on and runs into the long-on rope, 46 ball fifty for Williamson
pulled and it skids on a bit taking a top edge but safe, wide of short third man
tossed up outside off, Williamson forward pressing to cover-point
down the track and gets this just over mid-on for another boundary
four more, Williamson rocks back and flicks this wide of mid-on, three boundaries through the same region
spins away and Williamson goes to late cut but wasn't trying to get it this fine, comes off a fine outside edge and slips away from short third man
length ball at the pads, this is clipped down to long leg
fuller length at the off stump, played forward to and gets a thick outside edge to backward point
wide line outside off, cut at and missed, penalised
foot outside off, Williamson plays his calm dab down to third man for a little single
down the leg side, swung at and missed
back just outside off, Taylor sitting in the crease trying to force through the off side plays and misses
tighter line, forced out to backward point this time
full length driven up wide of mid-on and they get a quick single
drifts down the leg side, a little touch evades Buttler and slips away for three
full on the stumps, this is flicked out through midwicket
just outside off now, this is flicked down to long-on
forward lean, touches this down to long-on
straighter line worked out to deep midwicket
another forward press down to the ground to long-on, brings the hundred partnership up
back of a length, pulled out wide of long leg
just outside off, taps this into the covers for a quick single
angled into off stump, this is defended back to the bowler
straighter and this is tucked out through square leg for a quick single
goes to pull this and gets a thick inside edge into, oh dear, nasty, Taylor on the ground in pain
full length on the stumps, this is touched out to midwicket
full length, this is worked out through square leg for an easy single
full length, touched out through the same region
down the track, almost yorks himself and pushes this back to the bowler
goes back to try and cut this, off a bottom edge runs to cover
straighter, Williamson able to touch around the corner to milk another single
also turned through square leg, easy single and Taylor's fifty in 56 balls
length ball a shade outside off, this is driven out to deep cover
straighter line, this is clipped leg side in the air but short of midwicket going to his right
shorter length and pulled hard, excellent timing and wide of deep square, great shot
full just outside off, this is worked with the angle straight to midwicket
straighter line on a length, finds midwicket yet again
full length just outside off, Taylor angles this down to third man
starts wide, spins wider and this is called wide
down the wicket, drives off a thick inside edge down to long-on
oh beauty, bit of drift in and then spins away to beat the outside edge, superb delivery
fuller length and a touch wider, this is driven to cover
leg stump line, Taylor taps this to the right of midwicket but no single available
back to cut from a shade outside off and finds deep cover
thrown up a little more, Williamson down the track, clipping this handsomely wide of long-on but the fielder does really well going to his right and saves the boundary

length ball a foot wide of off stump, this is driven hard and well saved at cover, Root then throws at the bowler's end and they get an overthrow that was almost four overthrows without superb work from Finn
tries to run this down to third man but finds backward point
back of a length outside off, Williamson up on his toes clipping this out to deep cover
Taylor replicates the same stroke to the off side sweeper

full toss that Williamson misses going to flick to leg, cry for lbw not out given but England try a review, this is probably slipping down but caught the pad on the full, no bat involved, Hawk Eye says clipping leg stump so it stays not out
back foot press out to deep cover
slider a foot or so outside off, this is pressed out to backward point
down the wicket, Williamson caught out and has to adjust to defend out on the off side
back to cut and gets this aerial but away from backward point diving to his right, skips away to the boundary, not in full control of that
down the track lifting this down towards long-on
floated up a foot outside off and spinning away, Taylor lets it go
back cutting this out to deep cover
short ball, Taylor hooks and it goes through to Buttler, there's an appeal for caught behind, England are convinced but not out given and there's nothing on Hot Spot or Real Time Snicko
not as short and outside off here, this is cut on the bounce to backward point
low full toss a foot outside off, this is driven to mid-off
bumper, too high and called wide
low full toss tapped out between both short midwickets
same line, bit of a half-volley here, slower ball picked and this is whipped over the midwickets
length ball at the stumps now, this is patted up back to the bowler
down the wicket, not to the pitch so just defends this out into the covers
straighter line and fuller, this is whipped leg side and a half-save from midwicket saves four probably
back to force away into the leg side but cramped up and just pats this back to the bowler
back cutting this out to deep cover now
full length just outside off, this is driven to the left of the bowler
straight drive this time having skipped down the pitched, timed so well and gets it inside long-on, top shot
defending in the crease here gets a thick outside edge through cover
full length at the stumps, this is driven to mid-on
wider on the bowling crease, full length at the stumps, this is worked inside mid-on and they take on the fielder for a quick single

angled in, Taylor playing forward and gets a thin outside edge dropped by Buttler! There was the chance, going with one hand to his right hand side, Buttler couldn't cling on, maybe could have gone with two hands, seemed to react late there, big miss
straighter line, this is turned to midwicket
forward pressing this back to the bowler now
back waiting for this is turn and dabs this backward of point for a quick single
forward around off stump, pressing off a thick outside edge in front of point this time for a run
down the track, dragging this against the spin to long-on for another single
googly, into the pads, this is tickled behind square leg for a single
leans for this outside off, meets it on the full and drags it over midwicket, finds the gap and gets two more
down the track and played over the off side, not in control of this, in the air for a long time but lands between deep cover and long-off running in, moment of fortune for Williamson there
touched off the hip down backward of deep square
bumper on line, Taylor ducks well
back foot punch from a foot outside off wide of mid-off for a quick single
low full toss, patted up to mid-off
short run up here, Williamson onto a full ball tapping this to mid-on's right, he dives and saves well

back of a length, pulled hard and dropped again! Burst through the hands of Ben Stokes at short midwicket, it is slammed at Stokes but straight to him and he got two hands up to it but just couldn't hold on, second life for Taylor
legspinner around middle, defended in the crease up the wicket
down the wicket, lifting this on the bounce to long-on
driven with the turn down to long-off from just outside off
Williamson down the pitch again, meets this on the full and plays to long-on once more
waits for the turn here and cuts out to deep cover
back flicking this out through midwicket for another single
length ball at the pads, this is clipped out wide of long leg for a quick couple and that is Kane Williamson's century, a superbly controlled innings, just what his side were after here
length ball just outside off, this is pressed off the back foot to cover
goes to pull this, gets a little cramped and it comes off the glove I think in front of square leg
too straight and drifting into the pads, this is flicked smartly wide of long leg and it runs away to the boundary
wide on the bowling crease, angled into the off stump, Williamson blocks in the crease
bumper, right on line, Williamson sways out of the way
full on the off stump, this is pressed out into the covers
tight fourth-stump line, dabbed down on the off side from the crease, they sprint a quick single
full length a foot outside off, Williamson forward playing from under his nose out to backward point
shorter and this is wheeled out wide of deep square going to his left, still just a single
fuller length around middle and off, this is tapped out into midwicket
shorter again, Taylor onto the length and hooks nicely away from deep square and this time they do get a couple
around the wicket, angled in on a full length, this is worked into midwicket
fuller length around off stump, Williamson forward tapping this out into the covers
waits for this and dabs down not far enough away from slip for a single
straighter and fuller, this is picked up out towards deep square, in the air but short of the deep fielder
angled down leg, a little tickle lands short of the keeper diving forward
low full toss around off stump, this is clipped inside mid-on and they take a quick single
worked off the pads to deep square
picks up a length delivery and lofts it over mid-on, completely in control
slower ball outside off, dabbed down to third man
a strangled appeal for lbw as Williamson misses his flick to the leg side, angling down the leg side and there may have been a scratch on it too
now he goes in the air as well, takes a full delivery outside off and flicks it high over midwicket...pitches and stops in the outfield
tucked to midwicket
uses his feet again and flicks this superbly over wide mid-on, effortless batting by Taylor who gave it a late flick of the wrists
and now it's over the off side, another full delivery around off stump and it's sent straight over mid-off's head
takes inside edge and pad to the leg side
angled in from round the wicket, takes a thick inside edge into the pads
dropped, and it's turning into a bit of a shambles in the field from England. Williamson driving on the up and it's a regulation chance for Wood at mid-off
takes the pad to the leg side
short of a length, 86mph, defended to the leg side
short and cut wide of a diving point, jump to get over the top of the ball and gets some serious power behind it...well wide of the fielder
worked through midwicket
beaten as he tries to open the face against a slower delivery
short and pulled to deep midwicket
another hundred! Short of a length, worked off his hip just behind square and he comes back for the second which takes him to back-to-back centuries...he's had some lives, but played very well
round the wicket, back of a length, pushed back to the bowler
that was a stinging drive, was in the air back at Willey so technically a chance but it would have been a stunning grab to his right
opens the face and runs it wide of slip
more pongo down the ground as Williamson lofts a full delivery clear over the straight boundary, didn't really seem to use that much power...first six of the innings
finally they hold a catch! And it was a tougher one. Williamson in a care-free mode, aiming over the off-side again, but this time picks out Wood who times his leap to take a good catch
stays round the wicket, full, angling into the pads, glanced fine and there was some bat involved
worked off around leg stump into midwicket
uses his feet and flicks this along the ground through midwicket
worked to the leg side
full on middle, nudged in front of mid-on
driven through the off side for another couple, the placement has been very good in this innings
taken at slip! Bit loose from Elliott, but nicely bowled...tossed up outside off, a hint of turn, Elliott plays a booming drive and finds Root
full and straight, Taylor working right across that one but finds midwicket safely enough
full at middle and off, defended to mid-on
worked off the pads into square leg
beaten! Pushed across the left hander outside off who feels for it without much footwork
plays this in the air, but it flashes through the big gap between second slip and backward point, wafting off the back foot
pushed down the leg side, a freebie England can't afford
full outside off, pushed on the walk just to the left of mid-off
back of a length, flicked out to deep square
chopped down to third man from outside off
short of a length at off stump, 85mph, defended back to Stokes
shorter delivery, a cutter at 71mph, worked into the leg side
short and pulled from off stump through midwicket, Hales makes good ground around the boundary
full at off stump, flicked towards mid-on
short of a length, deflected to the leg side
back of a length on middle and off, defended to the on side
punched off the back foot into the covers, Hales in action again as he dives to his right
touch fuller, onto the front foot this time and he finds cover
tight with a hit! A little pressure had built, Santner drove straight to cover and Morgan takes a long time to take aim and then missed
takes an outside edge wide of slip to third man
and he beats the outside edge with a good length ball that Santner is feeling tentatively for
latches onto a shorter delivery, cuts it over backward point
this time he heaves a fuller delivery from around off stump wide of mid-on, not especially elegant but perfectly effective
ah, that's the best of the lot, a text-book perfect drive threads the gap between cover and mid-off
a sharp bouncer hurries Santner into his pull and he gets a top edge but it falls into space
bonus runs, Willey from round the wicket and slides it leg side...misses everything - bat, pad and keeper - and is also called wides
huge appeal for a catch down the leg side! Excellent take, but given not out. Not called wide so must have hit something. Hot Spot shows it is thigh pad. Good decision
full and straight, driven to mid-off
pulls hard at a short ball, gets plenty on it, and only just falls of six at deep square
good catch at slip! Trying to finish it in a hurry. Drives at a fuller delivery and gets a thick edge which flies low to the left of Root
short of a length, flipped off his hip and places it nicely between deep square and long leg
full at off stump, driven in the air but through a big gap at cover
a bouncer over middle and leg which he ducks
pushed to backward point
shuffles inside the line and works it down to long leg
over the wicket, flicked in the air and nearly carries to deep midwicket
round the wicket, full outside off, defended to cover

another one goes! An ugly end to Taylor's innings. He has a heave across the line and gets an inside edge into his stumps. Just having a quick check of this, in case anything else knocked off the bails, but the ball was straight into off stump
confident start as he drives firmly to short cover
full at the stumps, flicked to mid-on
good line at off stump, 87mph, defended to backward point
full at off stump, defended with bat and pad together
good stuff from Wood, tight to off stump, Ronchi can only defend to mid-off
gets forward and punches down to long-on
tucked off the pads to midwicket
round the wicket, full at the stumps, dug out to cover
that's a sweet strike! A huge slog-sweep over deep square leg...that just about seals it
sweeps from outside leg to short fine leg
tucked down the ground to long-on
worked to midwicket
very neatly played by the debutant, gets down early and paddle-sweeps this deftly through short fine leg

well, it won't be Ronchi to finish it, either...tries to do it in one shot down the ground, but was deceived by a slower ball and sent the ball straight up in the air which is then taken by Roy from backward point
back of a length, calmly defended to midwicket
backs away to leg and carves a length ball down to third man
another slower ball outside off, Wheeler can only find short cover
full toss, driven into the off side and that levels the scores
and that is that! A club over of the off side from Southee does the job
